race.comment: PRIDE OF VENUS (6) resumes for the smart Taylor barn and is right up to this if presented forward. That's likely given she's proven fresh and has trialled well. Maps for a soft run, and she posted her best figure when winning over this distance at her only start at the track. Stablemate HENRY'S BLADE (1) resumed here over 1000m and was a run short. He has more to give and will use the inside barrier. Stewart rides and is building a potent record with the yard. COLE'S BEST (2) resumes for a new stable and has won 3/3 fresh. The extra gear comes off and he's good enough to make the finish. RUSSIAN SUMMER (7) was straight back into the winners' circle in a CL3 here as favourite  This is tougher but with average luck he'll be around the mark.
